claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for continuously producing elongated siding panels, said apparatus comprising:
a conveyor;
a plurality of mold plates formed of a rigid material adjacent one another and supported by said conveyor for forming the elongated siding panels;
a die for extruding a sheet of material onto said mold plates;
each of said mold plates having an upper edge portion and a lower edge portion with an intermediate portion therebetween;
a plurality of vacuum passages disposed within each of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion for vacuum-forming said sheet onto said mold plates;
said intermediate portion having an aesthetic pattern for imparting said pattern to said sheet of material with said adjacent mold plates having different aesthetic patterns;
said lower edge portion having a lower leg extending substantially perpendicular from said intermediate portion defining a horizontal plane; and
a projection portion between said lower edge portion and said intermediate portion extending beyond said horizontal plane for imparting a jagged pattern to said intermediate portion.

24. A mold plate for use in forming elongated siding panels having varied aesthetic patterns from a sheet of material, said mold plate comprising:
an upper edge portion and a lower edge portion with an intermediate portion therebetween;
a plurality of vacuum passages disposed within each of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion for vacuum-forming the sheet of material onto said mold plate;
said intermediate portion having an aesthetic pattern for imparting said pattern to the sheet of material;
said lower edge portion having a lower leg extending substantially perpendicular from said intermediate portion defining a horizontal plane; and
a projection portion between said lower edge portion and said intermediate portion extending beyond said horizontal plane for imparting a jagged pattern to said intermediate portion.

36. An apparatus for continuously producing elongated siding panels, said apparatus comprising:
a conveyor; a plurality of mold plates formed of a rigid material adjacent one another and supported by said conveyor for forming the elongated siding panels;
a die for extruding a sheet of material onto said mold plates;
each of said mold plates having an upper edge portion and a lower edge portion with an intermediate portion therebetween;
a plurality of vacuum passages disposed within each of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion for vacuum-forming said sheet onto said mold plates;
said intermediate portion having an aesthetic pattern for imparting said pattern to said sheet of material with said adjacent mold plates having different aesthetic patterns;
said lower edge portion having a lower leg extending substantially perpendicular from said intermediate portion defining a horizontal plane; and
a plug assist adjacent said conveyor having a plurality of mold inserts rotatably engaging adjacent mold plates as said conveyor is operated urging said sheet of material into at least one of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion as said sheet of material is vacuum formed.

39. An apparatus for continuously producing elongated siding panels, said apparatus comprising:
a conveyor; a plurality of mold plates formed of a rigid material adjacent one another and supported by said conveyor for forming the elongated siding panels;
a die for extruding a sheet of material onto said mold plates;
each of said mold plates having an upper edge portion and a lower edge portion with an intermediate portion therebetween;
a plurality of vacuum passages disposed within each of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion for vacuum-forming said sheet onto said mold plates;
said intermediate portion having an aesthetic pattern for imparting said pattern to said sheet of material with said adjacent mold plates having different aesthetic patterns;
said lower edge portion having a lower leg extending substantially perpendicular from said intermediate portion defining a horizontal plane; and
an L-shaped projection extending from said upper edge portion for forming an interlock.

41. An apparatus for continuously producing elongated siding panels, said apparatus comprising:
a conveyor; a plurality of mold plates formed of a rigid material adjacent one another and supported by said conveyor for forming the elongated siding panels;
a die for extruding a sheet of material onto said mold plates;
each of said mold plates having an upper edge portion and a lower edge portion with an intermediate portion therebetween;
a plurality of vacuum passages disposed within each of said intermediate portion, said upper edge portion, and said lower edge portion for vacuum-forming said sheet onto said mold plates;
said intermediate portion having an aesthetic pattern for imparting said pattern to said sheet of material with said adjacent mold plates having different aesthetic patterns;
said lower edge portion having a lower leg extending substantially perpendicular from said intermediate portion defining a horizontal plane; and
a cap pivotally connected to and extending from said lower leg forming a cap leg extending upwardly from said horizontal plane such that said lower edge portion has a generally C-shape.
